  "claim": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-hemolysis-model-adequacy",
    "type": "Claim",
    "name": "CFD model adequacy claim for absolute hemolysis prediction in Class III VAD",
    "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, implemented in OpenFOAM 9 with a power-law hemolysis constitutive relation (Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients), is adequate for predicting absolute hemolysis index (HI) values across five flow-speed operating points for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump in VAD service. This claim is grounded in an extensive body of supporting work: (1) a three-level mesh refinement study demonstrating grid convergence index (GCI) below 4% for HI at all operating points; (2) particle-tracking validation against published PIV velocity data from the FDA Critical Path initiative showing mean velocity error below 8%; (3) Monte Carlo sensitivity analysis over twelve uncertain input parameters quantifying a 95th-percentile HI prediction interval of ±22%; (4) cross-laboratory reproducibility data from four independent CFD groups; and (5) comparison of predicted HI against in-vitro hemolysis measurements at three flow rates with normalised RMS error of 0.18. The totality of this evidence, documented in the associated validation reports and uncertainty quantification log, supports the conclusion that the model meets the credibility requirements for its intended use as a primary basis for hemolysis acceptance decisions at MRL 5. All supporting analyses are archived in the project data repository and cross-referenced in the validation result records attached to this package."
  },
  "hasContextOfUse": {
